## Context

Seventeenth run — web search available. 10 projects active. Created 3 journal entries (#2547, #2549, #2551) and 1 task (#1548). No assigned tasks to process.

### Key findings recorded:
- **ts-neuroimmune-subtyping (journal #2547, task #1548):** Sun & Bai review in Frontiers in Immunology 2026 (doi:10.3389/fimmu.2026.1708940). Three immune pathways: PANDAS/PANS autoimmunity, Th17/BBB/microglia activation, gut-brain axis. Proposes IL-1RN genetic biomarker and TSPO PET. Gut-brain axis may be blind spot in current plan.
- **ts-striatal-interneuron-pathology (journal #2549):** Wang et al. basal ganglia snRNA-seq/snATAC-seq NOW PUBLISHED in Biological Psychiatry 98(3):260-270 (2025). PMC12255533. Previously bioRxiv preprint. Confirms ~50% interneuron loss, MSN metabolic dysfunction, microglial activation. Foundational dataset for project validated by peer review.
- **Monitoring (journal #2551):** Comprehensive status update across all tracked items.

